Amurka za ta ninka kudaden da take ba da wa fasaha ta wucin gadi
Bayan da kasar Sin ta yi aiki sosai a fannin fasaha na wucin gadi, Amurka ta kamata ta ninka kudaden da take bayarwa don gudanar da bincike a wannan fannin, in ji mai saka jari da kuma mai aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple, Kai-Fu Li.
Irin wannan sharhin ya fara ne bayan wasu sassan gwamnatin Amurka sun ba da rahoton game da AI, duk da cewa Amurka ba ta da tsarin dabarun bunkasa AI.
A halin yanzu, kasar Sin ta bayyana shirinta na shekara ta biyu: tana son zama a matsayi na 1 a fannin kirkire-kirkire a shekarar 2030.
"Ganin cewa sauran ƙasashe sun fi Amurka baya, zai yi kyau mu ninka kasafin kuɗin bincike kan AI, muna neman ƙarin ci gaba a cikin AI", in ji Li.
"A cikin wannan lokaci, an samu ci gaba mai yawa a cikin masana'antun masana'antu, kuma an samu ci gaba mai yawa a cikin masana'antun masana'antu", in ji Li.
Littafinsa Supermukaman Ƙasa: Sin, Silicon Valley da Sabuwar Tsarin Duniya da Hawton Mifflin Harcourt ya wallafa a wannan watan, shi ne babban darektan kamfanin Sinovation Ventures, wanda ke da hannun jari a cikin kamfanin Face++ na China.
A cikin shekarun 1980 ya yi aiki a kan tsarin AI a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon, wanda ya kafa mafi girma a wasan Otello na Amurka, daga bisani ya zama darektan zartarwa na Microsoft Research da shugaban ofishin Google a kasar Sin.
Lee ya san wasu gasar fasaha da Amurka ta gudanar a baya, kamar su Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency's Robotics Challenge a kan robotics, kuma ya tambayi lokacin da za a yi gasar ta biyu don taimaka masa ya sami mai zuwa.
